 on Quran: Allah have mercy on one who reminded me","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 25, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was listening to a man recite the Quran in the mosque and he said, \u201cMay Allah have mercy upon him. He reminded me of a verse I was made to forget.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5038, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 788 Grade: Muttafaqun\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15891,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/29\/more-reward-walk-masjid\/","url_meta":{"origin":31383,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Mosques: More reward for walking to the Masjid","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: A plot of land around the mosque was vacant, so the tribe of Salimah intended to move there to be closer to the mosque. The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was told about that and he said to them, \"I have heard that you\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11568,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/22\/jannah-salat-fil-masjid\/","url_meta":{"origin":31383,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Mosques: Paradise for regular Masjid attendance","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 22, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever comes and goes between the mosque, Allah will prepare his place in Paradise every time he comes and goes.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 662, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 669 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32614,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/03\/nawafil-salat-separated\/","url_meta":{"origin":31383,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Nawafil: Voluntary prayers separated from obligatory prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu\u2019awiyyah reported: When you perform the Friday prayer, do not pray another prayer until you have spoken or left the mosque. The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, commanded us to do that, to not connect two prayers together unless we have spoken or we have left.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37360,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/11\/salat-najwa\/","url_meta":{"origin":31383,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Prayer is a private conversation with Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bayadi reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, came out to the people while they were praying and they were raising their voices in recitation. The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, the one in prayer is in an intimate conversation with his Lord Almighty, so let one look\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42588,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/02\/counted-every-step\/","url_meta":{"origin":31383,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Masjid: Allah counted every step as a reward","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 2, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Ubayy ibn Ka\u2019b reported: There was a man who lived the furthest from the mosque, as far as I know. He never missed a congregational prayer. It was said to him, \u201cIf you buy a donkey, you can ride it during the dark nights and hot days.\u201d The man said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31383","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=31383"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"